Parliament, Monday, 26 March 2018 – A joint meeting of the Portfolio Committee on Water and Sanitation and the Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow be briefed by the Special Investigating Unit (SIU), Auditor-General of South Africa and National Treasury on the challenges facing the Department of Water and Sanitation. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 27 March 2018
	Time: 09:30
	Venue: V454, 4th Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE OF WATER AND SANITATION, MR LULU JOHNSON AND CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI For media inquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
